Distrust grew from failed historical actions:

Post-Berkeley fire (Clermont area): a proposition passed to build a pipeline from Marin for hill water supply. Voters approved it and property taxes were collected, but the city redirected funds to a fire station and other projects instead.

California State Fire Marshal initiatives from ~50 years ago included perimeter clearance concepts that didn't work in urban settings (can't maintain 50-100ft clearance in dense neighborhoods) and fireproof roof requirements in Southern California/Santa Ana fire areas. Fires have continued despite roof law changes.

Building & Evacuation Challenges
Berkeley completed a $500,000 evacuation study.
Current building solutions seen as inadequate: concrete construction is financially unsupported and introduces earthquake risk; wood houses remain fire vulnerable.
Evacuation should be prioritized over firefighting capacity.

Research Resources & Insurance
Suggested looking into hearing records from church protests where the fire department has testimony records with pro/con positions on fire safety measures.
Major fire insurance problems attributed to current regulations.
